<TITLE> Budget on air </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 9 (bdnews24.com)Finance and planning adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam began his televised budget speech at 3pm Monday, the second under this caretaker government, amid high hopes for a wider social safety net. The government is set to announce a budget of approximately Tk 100,000 crore for the coming fiscal year, with a proposal to allocate up to 15 percent of the amount in subsidising essential commodities, Mirza Aziz said Sunday. He told bdnews24.com that up to Tk 15,000 crore would be proposed as allocations for fuel, food and fertiliser. Spending on non-development sectors, including food, structural coordination and loans, will exceed Tk 70,000 crore but the overall budget deficit will not be more than five percent, the finance adviser said. He said the government would not increase rates of tax in the next fiscal year but import duty on some goods might be hiked in the interests of local industry. bdnews24.
